Turn it up to 11.11.11
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
10th St is BACK for its first big event after remodeling!! COME CHECK IT OUT!! The numbers all go to eleven. Look, right across the board, eleven, eleven, eleven and... - Nigel Tufnel Come celebrate 11.11.11 with us in true Spinal Tap style! We will begin the night with some rock / acoustic music and then at the hour of 11 and minute of eleven will toast to the rock gods SPINAL TAP! After the toast we will have DJs spinning you some funky tunes till the early hours of the morning! Line Up will be posted Wednesday! Don't miss out! Entry charge will be $11 - $30 suggested donation to cover all of the recent improvements that we have been doing to 10th St.
Friday, November 11, 2011 at 9:00pm - Saturday, November 12, 2011 at 12:00am in PST

NAPA'S BEST SUMMER PARTY IS ON OUR FRONT LAWN
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
Come on over! We’ve assembled all the must-haves for an epic and leisurely wine country afternoon, and we're throwing a party to welcome you to our winery estate. Your picnic blanket awaits. On the day's itinerary: insanely flavorful eats from Sneaky's BBQ in San Francisco, paired with our summer-friendly wines and ice cream scooped from our vintage farm/ice cream truck. Bluegrass tunes from The Old Way will bring a lively and festive backdrop to the day. Bring friends and start packing your sunscreen now. See you there! Tickets are $60. Purchase by July 14 to secure your spot on the lawn.
Saturday, August 16, 2014, 1 PM - 4 PM in PDT
Turnbull Wine Cellars

Come get a drink with The Spring! Why? Because it's hump day. Because it's the day before Halloween. Do you really need a reason? We'll be there from 5:30 onwards. Let's hang. < less = more > with Dan Sherman, Alex Blackstock, Ian Ward Comfort
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
< less = more > sexy minimal + bass, every 1st Tuesday at 222 Hyde Less is More is back in action at their favorite club in San Francisco. This month, our ears and feet can't wait to welcome the deep soundscapes and irresistible grooves of Dan Sherman. Residents Alex Blackstock and Ian Ward Comfort have been packing their crates for a night of fun and finesse in dance music, bringing you the freshest cuts of sexy minimal and bass music from Berlin to Bristol. $5. 10pm - 2am.
